Meg Lemonnier https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meg_Lemonnier 0 Marguerite Gabrielle Lemonnier (née Clark; 15 May 1905 – 12 June 1988) was a British-born French singer and film actress. Lemonnier played the female lead in the comedy George and Georgette (1933).
